channel.description: i have the latest version of jdk but when i try to compile allstar source, it says i need to have jdk5 or 6, i dont know whats happening

item.title: Jdk
item.dc:creator: @Johnnyboy93 Johnnyboy93
item.description:
@Johnnyboy93 wrote:

Here is my compiler. It is the best compiler I have ever had.

@echo off if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error) :compile for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe") if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java) if defined p (goto end) :error echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. "%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe" http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp :end echo Finished! pause exit

I hoped this helped.

item.title: Jdk
item.dc:creator: @power_on power_on
item.description:
@power_on wrote:

This question has been repeated time and time again, but to fix it all you have to do is edit the compiler with notepad and change the file path coded to your version.

... set pro=%programfiles%\Java\jdk1.6.0_12 set pro2=%programfiles%\Java\jdk1.6.0_12 set jac=\bin\javac.exe set jav=\bin\java.exe etc
